observations.recommendation:
We recommended AAR and the Management agreed to direct the following:
a) Municipal General Services Officer:
i. Conduct complete physical count and classify properly the accounts presented in the RPCPPE;
ii. Maintain proper and complete records of the PPEs, particularly the stock cards and property cards in compliance with the applicable rules and regulations;
iii. Complete the disposal procedures of the remaining unserviceable properties in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency;
iv. Follow the procedures set forth under COA Circular 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020 for the one-time cleansing of PPE accounts of the LGU to establish the accountability, condition, and existence of PPEs;
v. Institute measures in the monitoring and controlling of the properties of the LGU.

We recommended AAR and the management agreed to:
a. Require the Local Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Officer (LDRRMO) and Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator (MPDC), Municipal Accountant and other officers involved in the implementation of the LDRRMF to fully implement the PPAs under the LDRRMF;
b. Ensure that cash advances to be used for DRRM-related expenses should only be granted to permanently employees designated as disbursing officer;
c. Require the Municipal Accountant to record the purchase and issuance of supplies to the appropriate asset and expense accounts which are charged against LDDRM Fund;
d. Submit the above-cited lacking documents pertaining to disaster risk-reduction related activities; and
e. Ensure that all disbursement vouchers and report of disbursements be properly supported with complete documentation before submitting the same to the audit team.

Based on the foregoing observations, we recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the ensuing department heads the enumerated courses of actions:
To the Municipal Accountant:
a. Compute or trace any discrepancy with the RPCPPE and prepare proper adjusting entries to correct the same;
b. Maintain a manual PPE Ledger Cards to record the custody, estimated useful life, depreciation, impairment and disposal of those assets;
c. Ensure that the accounting procedures were done in a timely manner, through proper time management and sound internal control, in order to achieve a fair presentation of financial statements.
To the Municipal General Service Officer:
a. Conduct a complete inventory count of all the properties of the Local Government;
b. Maintain proper and complete records of the PPEs, particularly the stock cards and property cards in compliance with the applicable rules and regulations;
c. Conduct proper procedures to dispose of the unserviceable properties, in coordination with the accounting department to derecognize the same in the books of the agency; and
Institute measures in the monitoring and controlling of the properties of the LGU.
